'''Suicide Tuesday''' (or '''Tuesday blues''', '''Ecstasy Tuesday''') is a slang term for the depressive period following the use of [[Ecstasy (drug)|Ecstasy]] or MDMA.

Ecstasy causes [[euphoria]] by stimulating the mass release of stored [[serotonin]] in the brain. This results in a depletion of serotonin reserves which can take several days to replenish. These low serotonin levels induce [[clinical depression|depression]] and can, in some cases, contribute to [[suicide]]. 

Hence, the name ''suicide Tuesday'' refers to the propensity of people to use Ectasy on Saturday night through to the late hours of Sunday morning, sleep off the effects on Monday, and go into depression on Tuesday. 

